From 5a06f567a18bb13e7f5dbcb0d0a3b36f6e7d0fce Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 16:36:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] init: skip mksandbox under OHOS_NATIVE_BOOT=1

In native chainload boot mode, OHOS init runs as PID 1 chrooted into
system_a. DoMkSandbox's unshare(CLONE_NEWNS) + chdir(rootPath) +
pivot_root + umount2(MNT_DETACH) + setns(orig_ns) sequence leaves
init's fs_struct->{root,pwd} pointing into a detached mount tree from
NS1. Every subsequent fork+exec from init then has a child whose
CWD/root inode is unreachable, and execv fails silently before
reaching userspace.

The chainload sets OHOS_NATIVE_BOOT=1 in init's environment so we can
detect chrooted bring-up here and skip the sandbox dance. Sandboxing
is a service-isolation feature, not required for the chainload
bring-up path.

Change-Id: I08ffee5d8a974a53980c40766b933c0f72a30d1e
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 services/init/standard/init_cmds.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/services/init/standard/init_cmds.c b/services/init/standard/init_cmds.c
index 08da2516..1633681d 100755
--- a/services/init/standard/init_cmds.c
+++ b/services/init/standard/init_cmds.c
@@ -963,6 +963,18 @@ static void DoSwapon(const struct CmdArgs *ctx)
 
 static void DoMkSandbox(const struct CmdArgs *ctx)
 {
+    /* Native chainload boot (init runs chrooted into system_a): the
+     * unshare+chdir+pivot_root+umount2+setns sequence below leaves init's
+     * fs_struct->{root,pwd} pointing into a detached mount tree.  Every
+     * subsequent fork+exec from init then has a child whose CWD/root
+     * inode is unreachable, and `execv` fails silently before reaching
+     * userspace.  The chainload sets OHOS_NATIVE_BOOT=1 so we can detect
+     * this mode here and skip sandboxing — sandboxing is for service
+     * isolation in a normal native boot, not required for the chainload
+     * bring-up path. */
+    if (getenv("OHOS_NATIVE_BOOT") != NULL) {
+        return;
+    }
     INIT_LOGV("Do make sandbox start");
     const char *sandbox = ctx->argv[0];
     InitDefaultNamespace();
